The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	Nagpur, Aug. 22 (PTI): Three Shiv Sena activists have been arrested for allegedly placing a piglet on the table of a civic official here on Sunday to draw his attention towards the pig menace in their area. The police have booked 12 Shiv Sena activists in all under relevant sections of IPC and Bombay Police Act the case          while Deputy Mayor Shekhar Sawarbandhe, who belongs to Sena, has denied any direct link of the party with the incident.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): Atal Bihari Vajpayee underwent a routine check-up of his wind pipe at the All India Institute of Medical Sciences on Sunday. Vajpayee, 86, was taken to the premier institute around 10.45am and was there for about one and a half hours.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): Heavy rain continued to lash Delhi, raising the water levels in the Yamuna river and prompting authorities to shift people living in low-lying areas and near the river bank. The Yamuna is now flowing 22cm above the danger level of 204.83 metres.                  
	 Madurai (PTI): Seven youths, including the boyfriend of a 17-year old girl, who allegedly outraged her modesty prompting her to commit suicide have been arrested, police said. A suicide note found by her parents in her notebook stated that she decided to end her life after being betrayed by her lover.                  
	Rameswaram (PTI): Two Sri Lankan fishermen have been rescued by Indian fishermen and brought here after they were found unconscious in their boat at sea, police said. The two have been handed over to Indian naval personnel, who have handed them over to police for questioning.                   
	Kannur (PTI): The controversial mangrove theme park set up by a CPM run co-operative here was reopened on Sunday after Kerala High Court granted a stay on the closure order. The park was shut down by the Centre last month on ecological grounds.                                                                                                                                              
